"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-closing-ceremony-tom-cruise-snoop-dogg-billie-eilish-paris-los-angeles-b1175937.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Under a slowly rusting Parisian sky, an Olympic Games that saw breakdancers light up La Concorde, beach volleyball players cavort beneath the Eiffel Tower andSnoop Doggtrot into the gardens of Versailles clad in full equestrian garb was brought to a glittering close at the Stade de France on Sunday night.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 0.9999899276060885, \"rank\": 1.0072495387616355e-05, \"text\": \"Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 438, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.391809095847523e-13, \"text\": \"Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 462, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9996525373076796, \"rank\": 0.0003475830479571554, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seemed fitting that the last word should go to the ubiquitous Californian rapper, albeit by video link, to fan the final embers of a heatwave Games that started down the course of a rain-lashed River Seine, but ultimately succeeded in bringing the Olympic spirit back to the streets.\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the soulless concrete bowls of an ill-conceived Olympic Park on the outskirts of Rio, and the Covid-enforced anonymity of Tokyo, Paris levered its iconic landmarks into front and centre of a Games to which the fans flocked by tram, by Metro and by electric bike.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999502198419353, \"rank\": 4.9782636681443805e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999992463720557, \"rank\": 7.536280783585912e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586801599565944e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Paris underscored one particular legacy for the at times turbulent 12-year reign of outgoing International Olympic Committee (IOC) president Thomas Bach, it may well have been his overseeing of the expansion of the urban programme that once again provided some of the Games' most indelible memories.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586801599565944e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, long Europe's epicentre of hip-hop culture, proved the perfect city to showcase that shift in focus, at a time when precarious geo-politics and especially the ongoing rancour with Russia make the relevance of the Games far from certain, and the accent on youth more important than ever.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586801599565944e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999997324430654, \"rank\": 1.523708922286124e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watched by an admiring Bach at stage-side, 25-year-old B-girl Ami top-rocked and froze her way to theOlympics' first breakdancing gold, while Australia's Arisa Trew won a skateboarding event that included a Chinese competitor who was born two weeks after the conclusion of London 2012.\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1733, \"end\": 1737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.661188182093988e-15, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.2711131835747104e-12, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1864, \"end\": 1869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3564108058411629e-18, \"text\": \"Arisa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\"}, {\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999462612155848, \"rank\": 5.1429283099911425e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.35872223321163e-15, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Off the Corniche in Marseille,Britain's Ellie Aldridge made light of a lack of wind to zoom to the very first kite-surfing gold, whilst almost 10,000 miles away off the Teahupo'o reef in Tahiti, a photographer caught the moment when a Brazilian world champion surfer appeared to walk on water.\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Corniche\", \"score\": 0.9924983868566732, \"rank\": 0.007554900571978533, \"text\": \"Corniche\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Corniche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Corniche\"}, {\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999996280167, \"rank\": 3.7206893888391355e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9891001368734722, \"rank\": 0.011019974822097763, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"score\": 0.9999624871740183, \"rank\": 3.751423188075739e-05, \"text\": \"Ellie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\"}, {\"begin\": 2043, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9976335388141312, \"rank\": 0.0020292652128582707, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}, {\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 4.973065318045964e-13, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One hundred years after the last Games were staged in Paris, fans roared the successes of home favourites including judoka Teddy Riner and rugby hero Antoine Dupont.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2346, \"end\": 2351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586801599565944e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2415, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}, {\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Antoine Dupont\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles made a triumphant return after the personal turmoil of Tokyo, but along with the superstars came the inevitable controversy.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999992463720557, \"rank\": 7.536280783585912e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the phalanx of flagbearers ushered in to start the ceremony on Sunday wereboxing gold medalists Imane Khelifand Lin Yu-Ting, of Algeria and Chinese Taipei respectively, whose gender was impugned in an unseemly episode that extended well beyond the confines of the boxing ring at the North Paris Arena.\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2715, \"end\": 2726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999995218796591, \"rank\": 4.481360150067804e-07, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"score\": 0.999999864925494, \"rank\": 1.3507437687112047e-07, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afforded the honour for Team GB were trampoline gold medalist Bryony Page and defending triathlon champion Alex Yee, two bright spots for the British in a Games that was speckled with silver linings.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3013, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 3048, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9971414286770363, \"rank\": 0.0028663874469793764, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  A plunge down the official medal tableto finish beneath France and the Netherlands will count for little outside the confines of the British Olympic Association (BOA) and UK Sport, whose near-\\u00a3250 million of funding for the cycle will be rightfully reviewed.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3406, \"end\": 3412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999872634363, \"rank\": 1.0482864342551881e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3421, \"end\": 3432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999999649407989, \"rank\": 3.0400586104559185e-08, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 3483, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3512, \"end\": 3515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0664522044675873e-16, \"text\": \"BOA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3521, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But those who broke through back home did not necessarily need to step atop the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For every glorious Bryony-bounce and lung-bursting Keely Hodgkinson charge there were heroic near-misses and heart-warming stories offered by the likes of weightlifter Emily Campbell and shooting mum Amber Rutter.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3757, \"end\": 3773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3874, \"end\": 3888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A dark and at times melancholy ceremony drifted through a story of a Golden Voyager, who purported to take the take the watching world on a dreamlike quest to the very foundations of humanity, but the thousands of athletes ringing the Stade de France were itching for a party.\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4156, \"end\": 4171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was duly provided byTom Cruise, who skydived in from the top of the cavernous arena, and finally, belatedly, bizarrely, by Snoop himself, who having popped up everywhere in Paris for the best part of two weeks, re-appeared on the big screen safely ensconced back in the sun-kissed climes of California.\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4375, \"end\": 4380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586801599565944e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4493, \"end\": 4503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Californi